  "text": "RADX depletion induces resistance to poly (ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) inhibitors in the BRCA2-deficient cells and increases resistance of RAD51-depleted cells to HU, camptothecin, and cisplatin [CITATION_1] . Although still poorly understood, RADX appears to be a critical regulator of RAD51 at the stalled replication fork. How the cell balances RADX levels to enhance replication fork protection without induction of inappropriate fork reversal during unperturbed replication will be an important area of study (Fig. 4 B) .",
